entries.femaleVariant: Judy's embarrassing herself again.
Wonder why Sue even keeps her around.
You're kidding. Her virtus keep 'em comin', keep the lights on in here, that's why.
Pff. Club would make it off fame alone. Everyone knows Lizzie's.
Susie'd rather not test that theory. Can't blame her, either.
That's Susie for ya – showin' peeps who's boss.
Told me I was generatin' losses, then just said "Have a nice life!" and slammed the damn door. I don't got nowhere to SLEEP tonight.
She pisses you off, then she's right – can you fuckin' decide? Get a grip.
Still got your body, though, don't ya? Work it.
Don't think I do? Every enny I make gets eaten up by upgrades.
Now I gotta work the streets to pay back my ripperdoc.
Doll-chip's not all ya got, from the look o' things. Faceplate's high design, custom made. Whoa, tits, too.
I INVEST in myself. Still wasn't good enough, still told me I was "underqualified."
Aww. But what are we supposed to do about it?
I told ya. Want my room back. That's all.
Pff. That ain't how this works, honey.
So I said, "Fuck it" – got a doll-chip. Went to Clouds, said they weren't hiring no more.
Whoa, why the acid? Just makin' conversation, Jesus…
If you were a Mox, this'd be a whole 'nother convo.
Whoa… start again. What's it you want us to do, now?
Beat some sense into him. That don't work –  I dunno, use lead. I don't care. Just want my room back.
Your pimp threw you out, that it?
Makes me wanna pull my hair out. Kinda has to, though, right?
Feast your eyes on this, hm?
I don't wreck the dancefloor like I used to.
Think I just woke up one day looking like this? This is real life, not no fairytale.
I'm a woman. That demands sacrifice.
It's hard work, never easy.
Ya don't say… See, I've always been a woman.
Oh, so this is what fucking sororal solidarity looks like now? Locker-room digs?
Tell me, baby, do I look as fine as I feel right now?
C'mon now, don't be such a wet rag.
Come off it, Zoe. Man wants a woman with some class.
That so? Well then you can go home! Hahaha!
Welcome to real life, sister. Your words, not mine.
Back in the day we would've busted this joint to pieces.
Smashin' windows was my speciality.
We gettin' old – that what you're sayin'?
We? Speak for yourself. And that's not what I meant.
Just sayin', time's've changed. Used to tear clubs down, now we keep 'em standin'.
Hey, where you goin'? Nothin' to see back here.
Let it lie – Judy's friend.
You done with that bagulho?
Yep. Back to the bump-and-grind.
